Q1.   Write a python script to dispaly the number of days in a given month Number.
Ans.   mon=int(input("Enter a month Number: "))
       match mon:
           case 1:
              print("January 31 Days")
           case 2:
              print("Feburary 28 Days")
           case 3:
              print("March 31 Days")
           case 4:
              print("April 30 Days")
           case 5:
              print("May 31 Days")
           case 6:
              print("June 30 Days")
           case 7:
              print("July 31 Days")
           case 8:
              print("August 31 Days")
           case 9:
              print("September 30 Days")
           case 10:
              print("October 31 Days")
           case 11:
              print("November 30 Days")
           case 12:
              print("December 31 Days")
           case _:
              print("Invalid Month Number)
Q2.   Write a Menu driven program to following operation-Addition,Sub.,Mul.,Div.
Ans.   print("\t1.Addition")
       print("\t2.Substraction")
       print("\t3.Multiplication")
       print("\t4.Division")
       a=int(input("\t Select Your Choice: "))
       match a:
           case 1:
               b=eval(input("Enter a number: "))
               c=eval(input("Enter second number: "))
               print(a+b)
           case 2:
               d=eval(input("Enter a number: "))
               e=eval(input("Enter second number: "))
               print(d-e)
           case 3:
               f=eval(input("Enter a number: "))
               g=eval(input("Enter second number: "))
               print(f*g)
           case 4:
              a=eval(input("Enter a number: "))
              d=eval(input("Enter second number: "))
              print(a/d)
           case _:
              print("Invalid Choice!")
Q3.   Write a menu driven program with the following option
       (a) Check wether a given set of three numbers are isoscales triangle or not.
       (b) Check wether a given set of three numbers are right angled triangled or not.
       (c) Check wether a given set of three numbers are equilateral triangle or not.
       (d) Exit.
Ans.     (1) Check wether a given set of three numbers are isoscales triangle or not.
         (2) Check wether a given set of three numbers are right angled triangled or not.
         (3) Check wether a given set of three numbers are equilateral triangle or not.
         (4) Exit.    
         a=int("input("Select Your Choice: "))
         match a:
             case 1:
                a=int(input("Enter first side of triangle: "))
                b=int(input("Enetr second side of triangle: "))
                c=int(input("Enter Third side of triangle: "))
                if(a and b==c):
                   print("Yes it's an Isoscales Triangle:)
                else:
                   print("No! It'sn't Isoscales Triangle:)
             case 2:
                a=int(input("Enter first side of triangle: "))
                b=int(input("Enetr second side of triangle: "))
                c=int(input("Enter Third side of triangle: "))
                if(a==90 and b+c==90):
                   print("Yes it's an Right angled Triangle:)
                else:
                   print("No! It'sn't Right angled Triangle:)
              case 3:
                a=int(input("Enter first side of triangle: "))
                b=int(input("Enetr second side of triangle: "))
                c=int(input("Enter Third side of triangle: "))
                if(a+b+c==180):
                   print("Yes it's an equilateral Triangle:)
                else:
                   print("No! It'sn't equilateral Triangle:)
              case 4:
                 print("Exit!")
              case _:
                 print("Invalid Choice!")
Q4.    Write a python program which take user's age as an inut and display the category of person.
Ans.    age=int(input("Enter user's age: "))
        match age:
           case 10:
              if(age<=10):
                print("Kid!")
           case 20:
              if(age<=20):
                print("Teen!")
           case 30:
              if(age<=30):
                print("Young!")
           case 40:
              if(age>=40 and age<=60):
                print("Experienced!")
           case 50:
              if(age>=60 and age<=80)
                print("Seniour Citizen!")
           case _:
              print("Invalid Choice!")
Q5.    Write a program which take a number from user print Saurabh shukla if even,print Preetek Jain if number is negative odd,print Aditya Chaudhari if number is Positive odd number.
Ans.    a=int(input("Enter a number: "))
        match a:        #or if(a%2==0):
            case 20:
               print("\"Saurabh Shukla\" Founder and CEO of MySirG.com")
            case -35:   # elif(a%2 !=0):
               print("\"Prateek Jain\" Seniour Precident of Ineuron Tech.")
            case 45:    # elif(a%2 !=0):
               print("\"Aditya Chaudhari\" Educator of Ineuron Tech.")
            case _:     # else:
               print("\"Rajeev Kumar\"  Google S/W Eng.")
Q6.    Write a python program to check wether a given string is multiword or single word string.
Ans.    s=input("Enter a string: ")
        match s:
           case s if ' ' in s:
                 print("Multiword String")
           case s if ' ' not in s:
                 print("SingleWord String")
Q7.    Write a python program to check wether a given number is Positive,Negative or Zero Using match case statement.
Ans.    print("1.Check a given number is positive negative or zero"))
        a=int(input("Pess Key 1"))
        match a:
           case 1:
              n=eval(input("enter a number: "))
              if(n>0):
                 print("Positive!")
              elif(n<0):
                 print("Negative!")
              elif(n==0)
                 print("Zero!")
              else:
                 print("Not a number!")
            case _:
                 print("Invalid Choice~")
Q8.    Write a python script to check wether two given string are identical,first string comes before the second in dictonary order or first string comes after the second string in dictonary order.
Ans.    s1=input("Enter First String: ")
        s2=input("Enter Second String: ")
        match(s1,s2):
            case (s1,s2) if s1==s2:
                  print("Identical String" )
            case (s1,s2) if s1>s2:
                  print("{} comes after {}".format(s1,s2))
            case (s1,s2) if s1<s2:
                  print("{} comes before the {}".format(s2,s1))      

Q9.    Write a python script to check wether a given year is 
         (a) Non Century leap Year
         (b) Century Leap Year
         (c) Non Century non Leap Year
         (d) Century non Leap Year
Ans.    year=int(input("Enter the century Year: "))
        if(year%100!=0) and (year%400==0):
           print("Non Century Leap Year")
        elif(year%100==0) and (year%400==0):
           print("Century Leap Year")
        elif(year%100!=0) and (year%400!=0):
           print("Non Century Non Leap Year")
        elif(year%100==0) and (year%400!=0):
           print("Century non Leap Year")
           
Q10.   Write a python program to display day name on the basis of user liking a color,Ask user for his favourate color.
        User can answer in a sentence like"I Like Red Color". Assuming all color name entered by the user in lowercase,
        Use match case to display day name associated with the color.
        
Ans.    s1=input("What Is Your favourate Colour: ")
        l1=["yello","blue","red","orange","white","black"]
        for colour in l1:
              if colour in s1:
                     c=colour
                     break
               else:
                    c="other"
                match c:
                     case "yello":
                       print("Monday")
                     case "red":
                       print("Tuesday")
                     case "orange":
                       print("Wednesday")
                     case "white":
                       print("Thursday")
                     case "black"
                       print("Friday")
                     case "blue":
                       print("Saturday")
                       
                       
